{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874921014,"sessionID":"ses_2859de5fcffeACVHJyPDf0z2hj","part":{"id":"prt_d7a62d1f6001uo4UYaeCwrr52w","messageID":"msg_d7a62acb00010o5xPMv8vCsvhJ","sessionID":"ses_2859de5fcffeACVHJyPDf0z2hj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API\n\n## AR-016 вҖ” PicoD ж–Үд»¶з®ЎзҗҶ API\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the PicoD file management API that provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **File Upload/Download**: Transfer files between the host and sandbox environments with support for streaming large files\n2. **Directory Listing**: Browse and query files within sandbox workspaces with filtering and pagination\n3. **File Operations**: Create, delete, move, copy, and modify files and directories\n4. **Path Security**: Enforce workspace boundaries and prevent path traversal attacks\n5. **Quota Management**: Track and enforce storage limits per session\n\nThis API serves as the file system interface between the agentcube platform and the sandbox orchestration system, enabling secure, quota-managed file operations with full audit logging.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **FileManager Interface** | Core file management interface with CRUD operations |\n| **Upload Operations** | Single file upload, multi-file upload, chunked upload for large files |\n| **Download Operations** | File download, directory archive download, streaming download |\n| **Directory Operations** | List, create, delete directories; recursive operations |\n| **File Metadata** | Size, permissions, modification time, MIME type detection |\n| **Path Validation** | Workspace-relative paths, path traversal prevention |\n| **Quota Tracking** | Storage usage monitoring and limit enforcement |\n| **File Watching** | Optional file system change notifications |\n| **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for file operation failures |\n| **Integration Points** | Integration with status store for operation tracking |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Changes to the sandbox orchestration interface (AR-009)\n- Modifications to storage implementations (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n- HTTP server implementation (separate PicoD daemon)\n- JWT authentication layer\n- Command execution APIs (AR-015)\n- Real-time collaborative editing\n- Version control integration (Git operations)\n- File content search/indexing\n- Encryption at rest (handled at storage layer)\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | FileManager implementation | ~300 |\n| `pkg/picod/file_types.go` | File operation type definitions | ~120 |\n| `pkg/picod/upload.go` | Upload handling and chunking | ~150 |\n| `pkg/picod/download.go` | Download handling and streaming | ~150 |\n| `pkg/picod/path.go` | Path validation and security | ~100 |\n| `pkg/picod/quota.go` | Quota management and tracking | ~80 |\n| `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | File-specific error definitions | ~60 |\n| `pkg/picod/file_manager_test.go` | Unit tests | ~250 |\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    Client Application                    в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                      в”Ӯ\n                      в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ              PicoD FileManager API                       в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ  Upload()   в”Ӯ  Download()    в”Ӯ  List()                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  Delete()   в”Ӯ  Move()        в”Ӯ  Copy()                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  Mkdir()    в”Ӯ  GetMetadata() в”Ӯ  Watch()               в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ              Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                 в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### FileManager Interface\n\n```go\ntype FileManager interface {\n    // Upload operations\n    Upload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n    UploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n    \n    // Download operations\n    Download(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n    StreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    \n    // File operations\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n    Move(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n    Copy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n    \n    // Directory operations\n    List(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n    Mkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n    Rmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n    \n    // Metadata operations\n    GetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n    SetPermissions(ctx context.Context, req PermissionsRequest) error\n    \n    // Quota operations\n    GetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n    \n    // Watching\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### UploadRequest / UploadResult\n\n```go\ntype UploadRequest struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    SourcePath      string      // Path on host\n    DestinationPath string      // Path in sandbox (relative to workspace)\n    Overwrite       bool\n    ContentType     string\n    \n    // For chunked uploads\n    ChunkSize       int64       // 0 for auto-detect\n    TotalSize       int64       // Known size, 0 if unknown\n}\n\ntype UploadResult struct {\n    FileID          string\n    Path            string\n    Size            int64\n    Checksum        string      // SHA-256\n    UploadedAt      time.Time\n}\n\ntype UploadChunkRequest struct {\n    UploadID        string\n    ChunkIndex      int\n    ChunkData       io.Reader\n    ChunkSize       int64\n    IsLast          bool\n}\n\ntype UploadChunkResult struct {\n    ChunkIndex      int\n    ReceivedBytes   int64\n    UploadComplete  bool\n}\n```\n\n#### DownloadRequest / DownloadResult\n\n```go\ntype DownloadRequest struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    Path            string      // Path in sandbox (relative to workspace)\n    Recursive       bool        // For directories\n    ArchiveFormat   string      // \"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\" for recursive download\n}\n\ntype DownloadResult struct {\n    FileID          string\n    Path            string\n    Size            int64\n    ContentType     string\n    Data            io.ReadCloser\n    Checksum        string      // SHA-256\n}\n```\n\n#### ListRequest / ListResult\n\n```go\ntype ListRequest struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    Path            string\n    Recursive       bool\n    Pattern         string      // Glob pattern for filtering\n    IncludeHidden   bool\n    Pagination      *Pagination\n}\n\ntype Pagination struct {\n    Limit   int\n    Offset  int\n    Cursor  string\n}\n\ntype ListResult struct {\n    Entries         []FileInfo\n    TotalCount      int\n    NextCursor      string\n}\n\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Name            string\n    Path            string\n    Type            FileType      // file, directory, symlink\n    Size            int64\n    Permissions     os.FileMode\n    CreatedAt       time.Time\n    ModifiedAt      time.Time\n    Checksum        string        // For files\n    MimeType        string\n}\n\ntype FileType string\n\nconst (\n    FileTypeFile      FileType = \"file\"\n    FileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n    FileTypeSymlink   FileType = \"symlink\"\n)\n```\n\n#### DeleteRequest / MoveRequest / CopyRequest\n\n```go\ntype DeleteRequest struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    Path            string\n    Recursive       bool        // For directories\n}\n\ntype MoveRequest struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    SourcePath      string\n    DestinationPath string\n    Overwrite       bool\n}\n\ntype CopyRequest struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    SourcePath      string\n    DestinationPath string\n    Overwrite       bool\n}\n```\n\n#### QuotaInfo\n\n```go\ntype QuotaInfo struct {\n    SessionID       string\n    UsedBytes       int64\n    TotalBytes      int64           // 0 for unlimited\n    AvailableBytes  int64\n    FileCount       int64\n    MaxFileCount    int64           // 0 for unlimited\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Execution Flows\n\n### File Upload (Small Files)\n\n```\nUpload(ctx, req)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nValidate request parameters\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nResolve and validate destination path\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nCheck quota availability\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Insufficient вҶ’ Return ErrQuotaExceeded\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nUpload file to sandbox\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nVerify checksum\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nUpdate quota tracking\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReturn UploadResult\n```\n\n### File Upload (Large Files - Chunked)\n\n```\nUpload(ctx, req) - Initialize\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nValidate request parameters\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nCreate upload session\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReturn UploadID\n\nUploadChunk(ctx, chunkReq) - Repeat for each chunk\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nValidate upload session\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReceive chunk data\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nStore chunk temporarily\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nUpdate upload progress\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nIf IsLast:\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nAssemble chunks\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nVerify checksum\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nMove to final destination\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nUpdate quota tracking\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReturn UploadChunkResult\n```\n\n### File Download\n\n```\nDownload(ctx, req)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nValidate request parameters\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nResolve and validate source path\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Not found вҶ’ Return ErrFileNotFound\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nCheck if path is directory and recursive flag\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Directory + !Recursive вҶ’ Return ErrIsDirectory\n    в”ңв”Җ Directory + Recursive вҶ’ Create archive stream\n    в””в”Җ File вҶ’ Create file stream\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nStream data to client\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReturn DownloadResult with ReadCloser\n```\n\n### Directory Listing\n\n```\nList(ctx, req)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nValidate request parameters\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nResolve and validate path\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Not found вҶ’ Return ErrFileNotFound\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nQuery directory contents\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ !Recursive вҶ’ List immediate children\n    в””в”Җ Recursive вҶ’ Walk directory tree\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nApply pattern filter if specified\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nApply pagination\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReturn ListResult\n```\n\n### File Deletion\n\n```\nDelete(ctx, req)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nValidate request parameters\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nResolve and validate path\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Not found вҶ’ Return ErrFileNotFound\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nCheck if directory and recursive flag\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Directory + !Recursive вҶ’ Return ErrDirectoryNotEmpty\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nDelete file/directory\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nUpdate quota tracking\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nReturn nil\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Code | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed file operation request |\n| `ErrFileNotFound` | `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | Specified path does not exist |\n| `ErrPathNotAllowed` | `PATH_NOT_ALLOWED` | Path outside workspace boundaries |\n| `ErrPathTraversal` | `PATH_TRAVERSAL` | Detected path traversal attempt |\n| `ErrPermissionDenied` | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | Insufficient permissions for operation |\n| `ErrQuotaExceeded` | `QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | Storage quota limit reached |\n| `ErrFileExists` | `FILE_EXISTS` | File already exists (without overwrite) |\n| `ErrIsDirectory` | `IS_DIRECTORY` | Expected file but got directory |\n| `ErrNotDirectory` | `NOT_DIRECTORY` | Expected directory but got file |\n| `ErrDirectoryNotEmpty` | `DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY` | Cannot delete non-empty directory |\n| `ErrTransferFailed` | `TRANSFER_FAILED` | Upload/download operation failed |\n| `ErrChecksumMismatch` | `CHECKSUM_MISMATCH` | Data integrity check failed |\n| `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox environment not available |\n\n### FileError Structure\n\n```go\ntype FileError struct {\n    Code       string\n    Message    string\n    Path       string\n    Details    map[string]interface{}\n}\n\nfunc (e *FileError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (path=%s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Path)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Path Security\n\n### Path Validation Rules\n\n```go\ntype PathValidator struct {\n    WorkspaceRoot string\n}\n\nfunc (v *PathValidator) Validate(path string) (string, error) {\n    // 1. Clean the path\n    cleaned := filepath.Clean(path)\n    \n    // 2. Check for absolute paths\n    if filepath.IsAbs(cleaned) {\n        return \"\", ErrPathNotAllowed\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Resolve symlinks and check boundaries\n    fullPath := filepath.Join(v.WorkspaceRoot, cleaned)\n    resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPath)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Ensure resolved path is within workspace\n    if !strings.HasPrefix(resolved, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n        return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n    }\n    \n    // 5. Check for traversal patterns in original path\n    if strings.Contains(path, \"..\") {\n        return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n    }\n    \n    return resolved, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Security Measures\n\n1. **Workspace Isolation**: All paths are resolved relative to a sandbox-specific workspace root\n2. **Symlink Resolution**: Symlinks are resolved and validated before operations\n3. **Path Traversal Detection**: `../` patterns and absolute paths are rejected\n4. **Permission Checks**: File permissions are validated before read/write operations\n5. **Quota Enforcement**: Storage limits are checked before write operations\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | ~300 | Core FileManager implementation |\n| `pkg/picod/file_types.go` | ~120 | Type definitions for file operations |\n| `pkg/picod/upload.go` | ~150 | Upload handling and chunking logic |\n| `pkg/picod/download.go` | ~150 | Download handling and streaming |\n| `pkg/picod/path.go` | ~100 | Path validation and security |\n| `pkg/picod/quota.go` | ~80 | Quota management and tracking |\n| `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | ~60 | File-specific error definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/file_manager_test.go` | ~250 | Unit tests |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"crypto/sha256\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"io\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"path/filepath\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/sandbox\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pkg/sandbox` | Sandbox interface for file operations (AR-009) |\n| `pkg/store` | Status persistence for operation tracking (AR-012/13/14) |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager | File operations within user sessions |\n| CLI Tooling | `kubectl-agentcube cp` commands |\n| HTTP API Layer | REST endpoints for file management |\n| IDE Integration | File sync for remote development |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Upload (small) | O(n) | n = file size |\n| Upload (chunked) | O(n) | n = total file size |\n| Download | O(n) | n = file size |\n| List (non-recursive) | O(m) | m = directory entries |\n| List (recursive) | O(m) | m = total entries |\n| Delete | O(1) | Per file/directory |\n| Move/Copy | O(n) | n = file size |\n| Quota Check | O(1) | Cached value lookup |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Direct Sandbox File Access Without API Layer\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Simpler architecture; fewer abstraction layers; potentially better performance |\n| **Cons** | No centralized quota management; scattered permission checks; harder to implement unified audit logging; no support for chunked uploads |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” API layer provides necessary abstraction for quota management, security enforcement, and operation tracking |\n\n### Alternative 2: Use Standard SFTP Protocol\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Industry standard; existing client libraries; familiar to users |\n| **Cons** | Additional protocol complexity; requires SFTP server in sandbox; harder to integrate with Kubernetes patterns; quota management requires custom extensions |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Custom API better fits the agentcube architecture and provides more control over quota and security |\n\n### Alternative 3: Leverage containerd/cri-o File Operations\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Native integration with container runtime; potentially more efficient |\n| **Cons** | Runtime-specific; limited to runtime capabilities; harder to implement features like chunked upload |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Higher-level API provides better abstraction and portability across different sandbox implementations |\n\n### Alternative 4: Event-Driven File Operations\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Better decoupling; natural fit for async operations; good for file watching |\n| **Cons** | Higher complexity; harder to implement synchronous operations like download; more moving parts |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Direct method calls provide better control, simpler error handling, and are sufficient for the current use case |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Path traversal vulnerabilities | Low | Critical | Strict path validation; workspace boundary enforcement; symlink resolution |\n| Quota bypass via sparse files | Low | Medium | Accurate size calculation; check both apparent and actual size |\n| Memory exhaustion from large uploads | Low | High | Streaming upload with chunked transfer; configurable chunk sizes |\n| Concurrent modification conflicts | Medium | Medium | Optimistic locking; ETag/checksum validation; atomic operations |\n| Storage exhaustion from failed uploads | Low | Medium | Automatic cleanup of incomplete uploads; upload session timeouts |\n| Denial of service via many small files | Medium | Medium | File count quotas; rate limiting on file creation |\n| Sandbox integration failures | Medium | High | Graceful error handling; fallback to error status; retry logic |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all picod file manager tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/picod/...\n\n# Run specific test categories\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestUpload\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestDownload\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestPathValidation\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run integration tests (requires sandbox)\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -tags=integration\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n```\n\n### Manual Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/picod/...\n\n# Interface compliance check\ngo build ./...\n\n# Lint check\nmake lint PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Upload small file | Returns UploadResult with correct checksum |\n| Upload large file (chunked) | All chunks received, assembled correctly |\n| Upload to existing path (no overwrite) | Returns ErrFileExists |\n| Download file | Returns correct data with matching checksum |\n| Download directory (recursive) | Returns archive with all contents |\n| List directory | Returns all entries with correct metadata |\n| List with pattern filter | Returns only matching entries |\n| Delete file | File removed, quota updated |\n| Delete non-empty directory (no recursive) | Returns ErrDirectoryNotEmpty |\n| Path traversal attempt | Returns ErrPathTraversal |\n| Quota exceeded on upload | Returns ErrQuotaExceeded |\n| Invalid UTF-8 filename | Returns ErrInvalidRequest |\n| Concurrent uploads to same path | One succeeds, others fail with ErrFileExists |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [PicoD Design](changes/AR-016/design.md) вҖ” Detailed design document\n- [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md) вҖ” API specification changes\n- [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-016/tests.md) вҖ” Test specifications\n- [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) вҖ” Related command execution API\n- [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) вҖ” Sandbox orchestration system\n- [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) вҖ” Storage interface\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Kubernetes client patterns\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. вң… FileManager interface fully implemented\n2. вң… Upload operations support both single-file and chunked modes\n3. вң… Download operations support streaming and archive creation\n4. вң… Directory listing with filtering and pagination\n5. вң… Complete file operations (delete, move, copy)\n6. вң… Path validation prevents traversal attacks\n7. вң… Quota tracking and enforcement\n8. вң… File watching support\n9. вң… Unit test coverage >= 85%\n10. вң… Integration tests passing\n11. вң… Race detector shows no issues\n\n---\n\n*AR-016 вҖ” Module: pkg/picod вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775874920908,"end":1775874921011}}}}
